description:
&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work for a caring organisation that really believes in people, and wants to make a difference?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, we are seeking to a highly motivated Health and Wellbeing Nurse to be part of our Pathways to Recovery substance misuse team working across our Prison and Community services. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to employ a highly motivated Health and Wellbeing Nurse to work within the Pathways to Recovery substance misuse team across Warrington Prisons and community. As a Health and Wellbeing Nurse with Change Grow Live.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We treat every person as an individual, so being flexible, empathetic, understanding and a good listener are key. We are looking for an enthusiastic, focused and values driven team player with experience of working in substance misuse. While not essential, experience of working in a criminal justice setting would be desirable as this post covers HMPYOI Thorn Cross and HMP Risley prisons. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join an experienced team who provide a range of evidenced based interventions for those experiencing difficulties with drugs and/or alcohol as well as being committed to taking a positive and empowering approach to service delivery. The post involves working across 2 Prisons and the Community team therefore weekend cover and Bank Holidays are standard as part of the service team rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role provides an exciting opportunity to contribute to the development and performance of the service across all 3 settings. Our mission is to enable and empower individuals to achieve full recovery and independence, and the service works in partnership with Commissioners, Community services, Prison health care partners and the Prison establishment to achieve the best possible outcomes for the Clients in our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change Grow Live are committed to creating an inclusive environment, which celebrates difference and allows our staff and service users to flourish. We recruit the very best staff from a wide range of backgrounds, ensuring service user’s benefit from our diverse skills and expertise. We always work to the principles of fairness and equality of opportunity in all our recruitment processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As directed by the lead Nurse, and Services Manager, the post holder will participate on delivering clinical interventions, administration of medications. Ensuring that high standards of quality are achieved to deliver key outcomes in line with contractual arrangements and service user needs with a key focus on providing services that are safe, effective, caring, responsive and well led.  A full list of responsibilities our set out in the job description.  The post holder will be open minded and committed to effective joint working with key partner agencies to ensure effective communication and collaboration for the benefit of all service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for hard work and a passion for delivering excellent client focused treatment services, we offer excellent terms and conditions, and a comprehensive career development pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change Grow Live are committed to creating an inclusive environment, which celebrates difference and allows our staff and service users to flourish. We recruit the very best staff from a wide range of backgrounds, ensuring service users’ benefit from our diverse skills and expertise. We always work to the principles of fairness and equality of opportunity in all our recruitment processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to Enhanced DBS as well as advanced prison vetting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; This post will  include working bank holidays and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
